OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1781718499
OL,3,CLabour calls for shadow minister to be
OL,4,Csacked over PM arson attack 'joke'
OL,6,FA shadow Home Office minister should
OL,7,F"grow up" and apologise for making
OL,8,Fjokes about the Prime Minister's home
OL,9,Fbeing targeted in an arson attack,
OL,10,FDavid Lammy has said.
OL,12,FMr Lammy launched an attack on Matt
OL,13,FVickers in Deputy Prime Minister's
OL,14,FQuestions in the Commons on Wednesday
OL,15,F(17 June), accusing him of "promoting
OL,16,Fconspiracies" and having "laughed
OL,17,Falong to demeaning homophobic remarks"
OL,18,Fduring a recent TV appearance.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@IO]wD@\OUxD@MO]xD@ZOUyD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G1/11
